# OpenWeed MVP - Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your actual values.

## Database
```env
# PostgreSQL connection string (Neon recommended)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://username:password@host:port/database"
```

## Authentication
```env
# NextAuth.js configuration
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-secret-key-here"

# Email server configuration (for magic links)
EMAIL_SERVER_HOST="smtp.gmail.com"
EMAIL_SERVER_PORT=587
EMAIL_SERVER_USER="your-email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_SERVER_PASSWORD="your-app-password"
EMAIL_FROM="noreply@openweed.co"
```

## File Upload
```env
# UploadThing configuration
UPLOADTHING_SECRET="your-uploadthing-secret"
UPLOADTHING_APP_ID="your-uploadthing-app-id"
```

## Optional Services
```env
# Mapbox (if you want to upgrade from OpenStreetMap)
MAPBOX_PUBLIC_TOKEN="your-mapbox-token"

# Supabase (for real-time features)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="your-supabase-url"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="your-supabase-anon-key"
```

## Development
```env
# Set to development for local development
NODE_ENV="development"
```

## Production
```env
# Set to production for production deployment
NODE_ENV="production"
```

## Getting Started

1. **Database Setup**
   - Sign up for Neon (neon.tech) or use your own PostgreSQL instance
   - Copy the connection string to `DATABASE_URL`

2. **Email Setup**
   - Use Gmail SMTP or your preferred email service
   - For Gmail, generate an App Password in your Google Account settings

3. **File Upload Setup**
   - Sign up for UploadThing (uploadthing.com)
   - Get your secret and app ID from the dashboard

4. **Run the application**
   ```bash
   pnpm install
   pnpm db:push
   pnpm db:seed
   pnpm dev
   ```

## Security Notes

- Never commit `.env.local` to version control
- Use strong, unique secrets for production
- Rotate secrets regularly
- Use environment-specific configurations
